{"word":"H3594 - כִּיּוּן - Kîyûwn - kee-yoon' - Chiun","slug":"H3594","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כִּיּוּן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Kîyûwn"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kee-yoon'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chiun"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05DF; - k&#x0131;&#x0302;yu&#x0302;n</b> - <i>kee-yoon'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3559\">H3559</a>; properly a <i>statue</i>, that is, idol; but used (by euphemism) for some heathen deity (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor): - Chiun."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3591\">H3591</a>, <a href=\"#/H3592\">H3592</a>, <a href=\"#/H3597\">H3597</a>, <a href=\"#/H3599\">H3599</a>"}]}